Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on measuring bandwidth between cloud data centers and analyzing the resulting time series. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category as the paper deals with multiple cloud data centers and their behaviors. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the robustness of the cloud infrastructure. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) could be relevant as the paper touches upon the reliability and quality of service of cloud infrastructure. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) could be relevant as the paper applies factor analysis to extract generalities from the data.
